We start by extracting the relevant figures from the provided statements.

1. Return on Equity (ROE)
• Net Profit (from the income statement) = 56,497.85
• Total Owner’s Equity (end balance from the balance sheet) = 16,056,497.85
We can calculate the ROE (using end-of–period equity) as:
  ROE = (Net Profit / Total Owner’s Equity) × 100
  ROE = (56,497.85 / 16,056,497.85) × 100 ≈ 0.35%

2. Debt to Asset Ratio
• Total Assets (end balance from the balance sheet) = 21,098,887.48
• Total Liabilities: The balance sheet gives Total Liabilities and Owner’s Equity = 21,098,887.48 and Total Owner’s Equity = 16,056,497.85. Therefore, total liabilities = 21,098,887.48 – 16,056,497.85 = 5,042,389.63.
Then:
  Debt to Asset Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Assets = 5,042,389.63 / 21,098,887.48 ≈ 0.24

3. Gross Profit Margin
• Gross Profit (from the income statement) = 194,172.30
• Total Revenue = 547,392.30
Thus:
  Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit / Total Revenue) × 100 = (194,172.30 / 547,392.30) × 100 ≈ 35.46%

Now we present the final answer in the required JSON format.

{
  "solution": {
    "Return on Equity (ROE)": "0.35%",
    "Debt to Asset Ratio": "0.24",
    "Gross Profit Margin": "35.46%"
  }
}
